OL,3,CBurnham on track to become next PM as
OL,4,CLabour MPs overwhelmingly back him
OL,6,FA total of 322 Labour MPs have
OL,7,Fformally backed Andy Burnham to be the
OL,8,Fnext party leader on the first day of
OL,9,Fnominations, the party has said.
OL,11,FThe total means that there are only 81
OL,12,FLabour MPs left who could nominate
OL,13,Fanother contender, the minimum needed
OL,14,Fto get on to the ballot.
OL,16,FBut convention dictates that the
OL,17,Foutgoing leader does not nominate a
OL,18,Fcandidate, meaning in reality there
OL,19,Fare no longer enough undeclared MPs to
OL,20,Fback an alternative to Mr Burnham.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
